echo "		[1;36m³  [1;37mi[0mrc  - [0;36mshiftee[1;36m@[0;36mefnet[0m or [0;36mi||uzion[1;36m@[0;36mundernet  [1;36m³"
echo "		[1;36m³                                             [1;36m³"
echo "		[1;30mÀ[0mÄÄ[1;37mÄÄ[0mÄÄ[1;30mÄÄÄÄ[1;37mú                       [1;37mú[1;30mÄÄÄÄ[0mÄÄ[1;37mÄÄ[0mÄÄ[1;30mÙ[0m"
echo
sleep 2
if [ ! -e ~/.osiris.default ]; then
  echo "copying osiris default file to ~/ (needed if it's your first time loading)"
  cp ~/osiris/.osiris.default ~/
  sleep 2
  echo "done."
  echo "Now just add load ~/osiris/os.bx to your .bitchxrc, and you're all set =)"
else
  echo "~/.osiris.default exists"
  echo -n "Do you Wish to overwrite? (y/n)"
  read yesno
  if [ "$yesno" = "y" ]; then
    mv ~/.osiris.default ~/.osiris.default.back
    cp ~/osiris/.osiris.default ~/
    echo "ok, replaced old file, and backed up old file to ~/osiris/.osiris.default.back"    
  else
    echo "Ok, not Overwriting."
    exit 1   
  fi
fi
